                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/118: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-29T22:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1928—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Regret to inform you Congress adjourned today without acting upon Bill
                    authorizing subordination of lien and debt settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
